  <body>

    <!-- Navigation Bar -->
    <nav class = "navbar">
      <div class="nav-brand">
        <a href="/">Combat Fake Info</a>
    </div>
    <ul class="nav-links">
        <li><a href="/factchecking"><i class="factchecking"></i> Fact Checking</a></li>
        <li><a href="/education"><i class="education"></i> Education</a></li>
        <li><a href="/game"><i class="game"></i> Game</a></li>
    </ul> 
    </nav>

    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <header class="hero">
    <h1>Education about Misinformation</h1>
    <p class="info">Learn how to spot and avoid misinformation, read below</p>
    </header>

    <!-- Main Content Section -->
    <main class="content">

      <!-- Introductory Section -->
      <section class="intro">
          <p><strong>Don’t let fake news fool you! Use the following tips to critically evaluate anything you read online.</strong></p>
      </section>

      <!-- Tips Section -->
      <section class="tips">

          <!-- Tip 1: The Story -->
          <div class="tip">
              <h2>The Story</h2>
              <div class="tip-content">
                    <p>What are they trying to say? Is it an ad or a joke? Look to see if you can find the same story somewhere else.</p>
                    <img src="/images/white-hat.png" alt="Check the story" class="tip-image">
              </div>

          </div>

          <!-- Tip 2: The Author -->
          <div class="tip">
              <h2>The Author</h2>
              <div class="tip-content">
                    <p>Is it someone’s opinion or a fact? Real news will most likely have a link to the writer’s details. If there’s no author, dig deeper.</p>
                    <img src="/images/global-news.png" alt="Check the author" class="tip-image">
              </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Tip 3: The Website -->
          <div class="tip">
              <h2>The Website</h2>
              <div class="tip-content">
                    <p>Are there spelling or grammar mistakes? What’s the URL? Check if the URL is reputable (e.g., ending in .com, .gov, or .org).</p>
                    <img src="/images/web-link.png" alt="Check the website" class="tip-image">
              </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Tip 4: The Date -->
          <div class="tip">
              <h2>The Date</h2>
              <div class="tip-content">
                    <p>Is the story recent or old? It could be outdated or a copy of something that happened years ago. Be wary of automated posts from bots.</p>
                    <img src="/images/schedule.png" alt="Check the Date" class="tip-image">
              </div>
          </div>

      </section>

      <!-- Conclusion Section -->
      <section class="conclusion">
          <p>By following these tips, you can better identify fake information and ensure you're getting accurate news.</p>
      </section>

  </main>

